  </Placemark>
  <Placemark>
    <name>Hodges-Hardy House</name>
    <description><![CDATA[1100 Travis, Wichita Falls<br/><br/><b>Address:</b> 1100 Travis, Wichita Falls<br/><br/><b>Marker Text:</b> Local builders W. Lee Moore and James A. Richolt constructed this residence in 1893-95 for Samuel H. Hodges, an attorney and real estate investor. The late Victorian style house has a wraparound porch and Eastlake detailing. Hodges sold the property in 1910 to Dan Hardy, a merchant, oilman, and landowner. Hardy and his wife Myrtle were prominent philthropists and civic leaders. The house remained in their family for over 70 years. Recorded Texas Historic Landmark - 1984.]]></description>
    <Point><coordinates>-98.489867,33.909187,0</coordinates></Point>
  </Placemark>
